    link(rel='stylesheet' href='./styles.css')
  body
    div.title.tc.fl.w-100.pt2.white.dapgray
      table.pr4.pl4
        thead  
          tr
            th.w-20
              a(href='/').imgstyle
                img(src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aepyornis/dap-dr/master/dashboard/dapdrlogo.png')
            th.w-45.pl3
              p.f3.medtext.ma1.black-90 #{district.borough} #{district.name} 
            th.w-20.pr6
              p.f3.black OCTOBER 2017
    div.w-100.bg-black-10.tc.fl
      p.mv1.pl4 #{district.neighborhoods}
    div.fl.w-100.tl.pl3.mt2.f5
      a(href='/index.html').no-print Back
    div.fl
      div.fl.w-25.pl4.pt3.pb2
        - var mapurl = 'https://github.com/aepyornis/dap-dr/blob/master/dashboard/cdmaps/' + district.cd + '-01.png?raw=true'
          img(src=mapurl).fl
      div.fl.tc.pl4.pr5.w-75.lh-copy
        p.f6.tl.lighttext A monthly update of 
          span.highlight harassment and displacement risk in rent stabilized buildings
          span  in 
          span.medtext #{district.borough} #{district.name}
          span . Risk indicators include sales, HPD complaints, HPD violations, DOB complaints, and DOB construction permit applications. 
          span  Buildings that appear on multiple lists are coded 
          span.dapyellow.black.ph1 yellow
          span , 
          span.daporange.black.ph1 orange
          span , or 
          span.dapred.white.ph1.lighttext red
          span , based on the number of lists they're on.

        p.f6.tl.lighttext.no-print The 
         span.fakelink blue links
         span  let you click through directly to a property's 
         a(href='http://whoownswhat.justfix.nyc', target='_blank') Who Owns What
         span  page for owner info, 
         a(href='https://hpdonline.hpdnyc.org/HPDonline/provide_address.aspx', target='_blank') HPD building info
         span , 
         a(href='http://a810-bisweb.nyc.gov/bisweb/bsqpm01.jsp', target='_blank') DOB's Building Information System
         span ,  
         a(href='https://a836-acris.nyc.gov/DS/DocumentSearch/BBL', target='_blank') ACRIS
         span , or 
         a(href='http://nycprop.nyc.gov/nycproperty/nynav/jsp/selectbbl.jsp', target='_blank') property tax information
         span . You can also click a building address to view it in Google Maps.
        p.tl.f6.lighttext All buildings listed have registered stabilized units at least once between 2007 and 2016 (
          a(href='#notes').no-print Notes
          span ).
      div.fl.pb3.w-100
        p.tc.mb1.f6.lighttext If a building appears on more than one of the lists below in a given month it will be flagged: 
        table.ph4.w-100
          thead
            tr
              th
                img(src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aepyornis/dap-dr/master/dashboard/riskyellow.png').risks
              th
                img(src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aepyornis/dap-dr/master/dashboard/riskorange.png').risks
              th
                img(src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aepyornis/dap-dr/master/dashboard/riskred.png').risks
    div.fl.w-100.pt3.ph4.pb2.bg-black-10
      p.f3.tl.mt0.mb1 New sales of residential buildings last month
      p.f6.tl.mt0.mb3.lighttext.lh-copy A large sale price can mean the new owner plans to displace tenants to make more profit. Buildings on this list sold for more than $50,000, which we use as a proxy for "real" sales versus other types of transfers. 
        span.no-print Sales data is messy â€“ click a building's 
        a(href='https://a836-acris.nyc.gov/DS/DocumentSearch/BBL', target='_blank').no-print (ACRIS)
        span.no-print  link for more detailed documentation. 
        span.medtext Note: 
        span Data from the Department of Finance can lag, so these sales might be from the month before last. (currently September 2017)
      table.w-100
        thead
          tr
            th.w-10 BBL
            th.w-20 Address
            th.w-15 Total Units
            th.w-10(colspan="2").f5 Stabilized Units
            th.f5.w-5.tc Sale Price
            th.f5.w-5.tc Price / Sq Foot
            th.f5.w-5.tc Sale Date
            th.w-20 Owner
            th.w-10.no-print 
          tr
            th.tl
            th
            th
            th.w-5.gray 2007
            th.w-5 2016
            th 
            th.tl
            th  
            th 
            th.no-print
        tbody
        each sale in recentSales
          - var trStyle = rowClass(bblCount[sale.bbl].length);
          tr(class=trStyle)
            td.pr3.tl #{sale.bbl}
            td.tl !{sale.googlelink}
            td.tc #{sale.unitsres}
            td.gray.tc #{sale.uc2007} 
            td.tc #{sale.uc2016}
            td.tc $#{sale.saleprice}
            td.tc $ #{sale.ppgsf}
            td #{sale.iso_date}
            td.f7.tl.pr2.pt1.pl2 !{sale.owner}
            td.f7.tc.no-print !{sale.hpdlink} !{sale.bislink} !{sale.acrislink} !{sale.taxlink}
    div.fl.w-100.tc.mt4.ph4.pb2.bg-black-10
      p.f3.tl.mt3.mb1 Buildings with 3+ new HPD Complaints last month
      p.f6.tl.mt0.mb3.lighttext.lh-copy Complaints that tenants make about conditions in their apartment or building get sent to Housing Preservation and Development for inspection. One complaint can include multiple problems in an apartment or a building. 
        span.no-print Click a building's 
        a(href='https://hpdonline.hpdnyc.org/HPDonline/provide_address.aspx', target='_blank').no-print (HPD)
        span.no-print  link for details. 
      table.w-100
        thead
          tr
            th.w-10 BBL
            th.w-15 Address
            th.w-15 Total Units
            th.w-16(colspan="2") Stabilized Units
            th.w-15 Complaints
            th.w-20 Owner
            th.w-10.no-print  
          tr 
            th.w-10.pb3
            th.w-15 
            th.w-15 
            th.w-8.gray 2007
            th.w-8 2016
            th.w-15
            th.w-20 
            th.w-10.no-print
        tbody
        each complaint in hpdComplaints
          - var trStyle = rowClass(bblCount[complaint.bbl].length);
          tr(class=trStyle)
            td.pr3.tl #{complaint.bbl}
            td.tl !{complaint.googlelink}
            td #{complaint.residentialunits}
            td.gray #{complaint.uc2007}
            td #{complaint.uc2016}
            td #{complaint.hpdcomplaints}
            td.f7.tl.pr2.pt1.pl2 !{complaint.owner}
            td.f7.no-print !{complaint.hpdlink} !{complaint.bislink} !{complaint.acrislink} !{complaint.taxlink}
    div.fl.w-100.tc.mt4.ph4.pb2.bg-black-10
      p.f3.tl.mt3.mb1 Buildings with 10+ new HPD violations last month
      p.f6.tl.mt0.mb3.lighttext.lh-copy HPD issues violations of the Housing Maintenance Code after inspecting building conditions. Class A, B, and C violations can indicate a landlord is neglecting or actively harassing tenants, Class C being the most severe 
        span.no-print (
        a(href='http://www1.nyc.gov/assets/hpd/downloads/pdf/ABCs-housing-singlepg.pdf', target='_blank').no-print info, p.7
        span.no-print ). Click a building's 
        a(href='https://hpdonline.hpdnyc.org/HPDonline/provide_address.aspx', target='_blank').no-print (HPD)
        span.no-print  link for more details
        span . 
      table.w-100
        thead
          tr
            th.w-10 BBL
            th.w-15 Address
            th.w-10 Total Units
            th.w-10(colspan="2") Stabilized Units
            th Class A
            th Class B
            th Class C
            th Total
            th.w-20 Owner
            th.w-10.no-print 
          tr 
            th.w-10.pb3
            th.w-15 
            th.w-10 
            th.w-5.gray 2007
            th.w-5 2016
            th 
            th 
            th 
            th 
            th.w-20 
            th.w-10.no-print
        tbody
        each violation in hpdViolations
          - var trStyle = rowClass(bblCount[violation.bbl].length);
          tr(class=trStyle)
            td.pr3.tl #{violation.bbl}
            td.tl !{violation.googlelink}
            td #{violation.residentialunits}
            td.gray #{violation.uc2007} 
            td #{violation.uc2016}
            td #{violation.class_a}
            td #{violation.class_b}
            td #{violation.class_c}
            td #{violation.total}
            td.f7.tl.pr2.pt1 !{violation.owner}
            td.f7.no-print !{violation.hpdlink} !{violation.bislink} !{violation.acrislink} !{violation.taxlink}
    div.fl.w-100.tc.mt4.ph4.pb2.bg-black-10
      p.f3.tl.mt3.mb1 Buildings with 2+ new DOB Complaints last month
      p.f6.tl.mt0.mb3.lighttext.lh-copy Complaints that tenants make about construction or certain building conditions (e.g. broken elevator) get sent to the Department of Buildings. 
        span.no-print Click a building's 
        a(href='http://a810-bisweb.nyc.gov/bisweb/bsqpm01.jsp', target='_blank').no-print (DOB)
        span.no-print  link for details through the Building Information System. 
      table.w-100
        thead
          tr
            th.w-10 BBL
            th.w-15 Address
            th.w-15 Total Units
            th.w-16(colspan="2") Stabilized Units
            th.w-15 Complaints
            th.w-20 Owner
            th.w-10.no-print
          tr 
            th.w-10.pb3
            th.w-15 
            th.w-15 
            th.w-8.gray 2007
            th.w-8 2016
            th.w-15
            th.w-20 
            th.w-10.no-print
        tbody
        each complaint in dobComplaints
          - var trStyle = rowClass(bblCount[complaint.bbl].length);
          tr(class=trStyle)
            td.f6.pr3.tl #{complaint.bbl}
            td.f6.tl !{complaint.googlelink}
            td #{complaint.residentialunits}
            td.gray #{complaint.uc2007}
            td #{complaint.uc2016}
            td #{complaint.dobcomplaints}
            td.f7.tl.pr2.pt1.pl2 !{complaint.owner}
            td.f7.no-print !{complaint.hpdlink} !{complaint.bislink} !{complaint.acrislink} !{complaint.taxlink}
    div.fl.w-100.tc.mt4.ph4.pb2.bg-black-10
      p.f3.tl.mt3.mb1 Buildings with new DOB permit applications filed last month
      p.f6.tl.mt0.mb3.lighttext.lh-copy Construction permit applications show a landlord's intention to do construction and renovations, which can be used to destabilize apartments: for example, Alt 2 permits may represent work that will justify Individual Apartment Improvement rent increases 
        span.no-print (
        a(href='http://www1.nyc.gov/assets/buildings/pdf/pw1_userguide.pdf', target='_blank').no-print more info on permit types, p.5
        span.no-print ). Click a building's 
        a(href='http://a810-bisweb.nyc.gov/bisweb/bsqpm01.jsp', target='_blank').no-print (DOB)
        span.no-print  link for details through the Building Information System
        span . 
      table.w-100
        thead
          tr
            th.w-10 BBL
            th.w-20 Address
            th.w-15 Total Units
            th.w-10(colspan="2") Stabilized Units
            th Alt 1 Permits
            th Alt 2 Permits
            th DM Permits
            th.w-20 Owner
            th.w-10.no-print
          tr 
            th.w-10.pb3
            th.w-15 
            th.w-10 
            th.w-5.gray 2007
            th.w-5 2016
            th 
            th 
            th  
            th.w-20 
            th.w-10.no-print
        tbody
        each job in dobjobs
          - var trStyle = rowClass(bblCount[job.bbl].length);
          tr(class=trStyle)
            td.pr3.tl #{job.bbl}
            td.tl !{job.googlelink}
            td #{job.residentialunits}
            td.gray #{job.uc2007} 
            td #{job.uc2016}
            td #{job.a1}
            td #{job.a2}
            td #{job.dm}
            td.f7.tl.pr2.pt1 !{job.owner}
            td.f7.no-print !{job.hpdlink} !{job.bislink} !{job.acrislink} !{job.taxlink}
